Package com.blockhaus2000.minecraft.util.command.event

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CommandEvent<T extends CommandInfo>
    This is the main class for all CommandEvents.
    CommandEventPackage
    This Event is not a regular CommandEvent, because this will hold a bunch of CommandEvents that are fired within a command execution.
    IllegalSyntaxCommandEvent
    A CommandEvent that is fired if the syntax of a command is wrong/illegal.
    NoPermissionCommandEvent
    This CommandEvent will be fired if a command has been executed but the CommandSender does not have the required permission.
    NotEnoughArgumentsCommandEvent
    This CommandEvent will be fired if a command has been executed but the CommandSender does not have the required minimum arguments.
    TooManyArgumentsCommandEvent
    This CommandEvent will be fired if a command has been executed but the CommandSender does have too many arguments.
    UnknownSecondLevelCommandEvent
    This CommandEvent will be fired if a command has been executed but the second-level-command does not match.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    IllegalSyntaxType
    Specifies the illegal syntax type in the IllegalSyntaxCommandEvent.
